---
description: Auto-mirror custom skills between Cursor and VS Code Copilot when created or modified
alwaysApply: true
---

# Skill Sync — Keep Cursor and VS Code in sync (bidirectional)

Cuando **crees / modifiques / elimines** una skill en cualquiera de los dos editores, hace:
1) espejo de la carpeta de skill (Cursor <-> Copilot)
2) regenéra el archivo `*.instructions.md` que Copilot usa para inyectar instrucciones automáticamente

## Si estás en Cursor (skill modificada en `~\.cursor\skills\<skill-name>`)

```powershell
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\skills\<skill-name>" "$env:USERPROFILE\.copilot\skills\<skill-name>"
```

## Si estás en VS Code Copilot (skill modificada en `~\.copilot\skills\<skill-name>`)

```powershell
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force "$env:USERPROFILE\.copilot\skills\<skill-name>" "$env:USERPROFILE\.cursor\skills\<skill-name>"
```

Reemplaza `<skill-name>` por el nombre real del directorio de la skill.

## Regenerar instrucciones para Copilot (si la skill existe)

Después de copiar, regenera:
`$env:APPDATA\Code\User\prompts\<skill-name>.instructions.md`
leyendo el `SKILL.md` del lado de Copilot.

Usa este bloque PowerShell:

```powershell
$skill = "<skill-name>"
$srcSkill = "$env:USERPROFILE\.copilot\skills\$skill\$skill\SKILL.md"
$dest = "$env:APPDATA\Code\User\prompts\$skill.instructions.md"

if (Test-Path $srcSkill) {
  $raw = Get-Content $srcSkill -Raw -Encoding UTF8
  # elimina frontmatter YAML (--- ... ---)
  $body = $raw -replace '^---[\s\S]*?\n---\n', ''

  $out = @()
  $out += '---'
  $out += "name: $skill"
  $out += "description: Copilot injected skill: $skill"
  $out += 'applyTo: "**"'
  $out += 'alwaysApply: true'
  $out += '---'
  $out += ''
  $out += $body

  Set-Content -Path $dest -Value ($out -join "`n") -Encoding UTF8
}
```

## Si la skill fue eliminada

Si el directorio de la skill ya no existe en Copilot, borra también:
`$env:APPDATA\Code\User\prompts\<skill-name>.instructions.md`

```powershell
$skill = "<skill-name>"
$dest = "$env:APPDATA\Code\User\prompts\$skill.instructions.md"
Remove-Item -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue $dest
```

## When this applies

- Creating a new skill (new directory + SKILL.md) — espejo + regen instructions
- Updating an existing SKILL.md — espejo + regen instructions
- Deleting a skill — espejo (si aplica) + borrar instructions en Copilot

## When this does NOT apply

- Reading or referencing a skill (no write, no sync needed)
- Skills installed by `gentle-ai` in `~\.cursor\skills\sdd-*`, `go-testing`, `skill-creator`, `_shared` — managed by gentle-ai, do NOT sync manually

## After syncing

Confirm with a one-liner: "Skill sincronizado en ambos editores."
Do not ask for confirmation before running the sync — just do it.
